76374 - Neo-Jadarite This mineral is morphologically similar to the nesosilicate Jadarite but shows subtle differences owing to the process by which radioactive neutron deposition altered the asteroid ore from which it has been extrated. Neo-Jadarite shares with its morphotype a relatively plentiful amount of lithium and boron in its chemical composition, making this mineral highly desirable for a number of industrial processes.

Neo-Jadarite is most readily found in Nesosilicate Rakovene ore obtained from fields scattered across the Triglavian-occupied region of Pochven.		 Mineral

76941 - Vila Allopoiesis Node A single node of the Vila Allopoiesis Nexus receiving materials and constructing Mutadaptive Construction Components in order to serve the inscrutable purposes of the Triglavian masters of the subverted rogue drones tending it. The drones and their automated Vila Allopoiesis Nodes are ceaselessly at work churning out the general purpose Mutadaptive Construction Components that are used in the construction of many Triglavian structures and devices.

Hacking this Vila Allopoiesis Node is likely to give access to some portion of the data, materials and ancillary devices used in its functions. Care should be taken to avoid or destroy the Vila Skarbnik drone variants guarding the location, apparently the custodians and workhorses of the nexus and the asteroid fields from which the facility sources its materials. 76951 - Ishtar Zydrine Burn SKIN Zydrine Burn is a potent liquor that is loosely related to the more refined Zydrine Wine, both of these green-hued drinks being produced using rice leaves, a certain portion of the grains, and whatever additives are appropriate to the style of drink. While Zydrine Wine can be an extraordinarily delicate and subtle drink, with the finest generally held to be brewed from the rice plants of Intaki Prime, its more powerful cousin is a somewhat pungent and vividly green brew. Rumors suggest that some versions of Zydrine Burn use as ingredients effluent from Quafe production, liquefied fedo scent glands, or even the notorious protein delicacies in powdered form. Whatever the case, a market for this harshly memorable liquor has sprung up among space workers of all kinds, and few space station bars lack a bottle or two of the stuff. Among planetary populations the brew has a more notorious reputation, popularly considered the tipple of underclasses, criminals, and ruthless capsuleer pirates. Permanent SKIN

76954 - Ishkur Zydrine Burn SKIN Zydrine Burn is a potent liquor that is loosely related to the more refined Zydrine Wine, both of these green-hued drinks being produced using rice leaves, a certain portion of the grains, and whatever additives are appropriate to the style of drink. While Zydrine Wine can be an extraordinarily delicate and subtle drink, with the finest generally held to be brewed from the rice plants of Intaki Prime, its more powerful cousin is a somewhat pungent and vividly green brew. Rumors suggest that some versions of Zydrine Burn use as ingredients effluent from Quafe production, liquefied fedo scent glands, or even the notorious protein delicacies in powdered form. Whatever the case, a market for this harshly memorable liquor has sprung up among space workers of all kinds, and few space station bars lack a bottle or two of the stuff. Among planetary populations the brew has a more notorious reputation, popularly considered the tipple of underclasses, criminals, and ruthless capsuleer pirates. Permanent SKIN

648314 Vila Skarbnik variants of Triglavian-controlled rogue drones patrol the Vila Allopoiesis Nexus sites and the Nesosilicate Rakovene fields from which the Triglavians' automated industrial facilities source much of their materials. 648383 Zydrine Burn Zydrine Burn
648384 Zydrine Burn is a potent liquor that is loosely related to the more refined Zydrine Wine, both of these green-hued drinks being produced using rice leaves, a certain portion of the grains, and whatever additives are appropriate to the style of drink. While Zydrine Wine can be an extraordinarily delicate and subtle drink, with the finest generally held to be brewed from the rice plants of Intaki Prime, its more powerful cousin is a somewhat pungent and vividly green brew. Rumors suggest that some versions of Zydrine Burn use as ingredients effluent from Quafe production, liquefied fedo scent glands, or even the notorious protein delicacies in powdered form. Whatever the case, a market for this harshly memorable liquor has sprung up among space workers of all kinds, and few space station bars lack a bottle or two of the stuff. Among planetary populations the brew has a more notorious reputation, popularly considered the tipple of underclasses, criminals, and ruthless capsuleer pirates. While Zydrine Wine can be an extraordinarily delicate and subtle drink, with the finest generally held to be brewed from the rice plants of Intaki Prime, its more powerful cousin is a somewhat pungent and vividly green brew. Rumors suggest that some versions of Zydrine Burn use as ingredients effluent from Quafe production, liquefied fedo scent glands, or even the notorious protein delicacies in powdered form. Whatever the case, a market for this harshly memorable liquor has sprung up among space workers of all kinds, and few space station bars lack a bottle or two of the stuff.
